"title": "2351: Jesus Christ, miracles of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2351",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Supernatural acts of Jesus Christ, revealing and confirming his Messianic credentials, and the coming of God's kingdom. The miracles of Christ are to be seen as an integral part of his ministry.</p>\n<h2>Examples of the kind of miracles Jesus Christ performed</h2>\n<h3>Authority over natural forces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:27\">MAT 8:27</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:41\">MRK 4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:25\">LUK 8:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:19-Matt14:20\">MAT 14:19–14:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:41-Mark6:43\">MRK 6:41–6:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:16-Luke9:17\">LUK 9:16–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:11-John6:13\">JHN 6:11–6:13</a> <em>the feeding of 5,000</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:25\">MAT 14:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:48\">MRK 6:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:19\">JHN 6:19</a> <em>Jesus Christ walks on water</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:27\">MAT 17:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:4\">LUK 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:6\">LUK 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:9\">JHN 2:9</a> <em>Jesus Christ turns water into wine.</em></p>\n<h3>Healing the sick</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:24\">MAT 4:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:13\">MAT 8:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:10\">LUK 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:15\">MAT 8:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:31\">MRK 1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:39\">LUK 4:39</a> <em>Simon's mother-in-law</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:22\">MAT 9:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:29\">MRK 5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:44\">LUK 8:44</a> <em>the woman with the issue of blood</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:29-Matt9:30\">MAT 9:29–9:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:13\">MAT 12:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:5\">MRK 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:10\">LUK 6:10</a> <em>the man with a shrivelled hand</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:35\">MRK 7:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:14\">LUK 17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:52-John4:53\">JHN 4:52–4:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:8-John5:9\">JHN 5:8–5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:6-John9:7\">JHN 9:6–9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Casting out demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:18\">MAT 17:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25-Mark9:26\">MRK 9:25–9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:42\">LUK 9:42</a></p>\n<h3>Raising the dead</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14-Luke7:15\">LUK 7:14–7:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:25\">MAT 9:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:41-Mark5:42\">MRK 5:41–5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:54-Luke8:55\">LUK 8:54–8:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:43-John11:44\">JHN 11:43–11:44</a></p>\n<h2>The purpose of Jesus Christ's miracles</h2>\n<h3>To bring healing and wholeness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:28\">MAT 15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:14-Luke17:15\">LUK 17:14–17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:38\">JHN 9:38</a></p>\n<h3>To reveal God's kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:28\">MAT 12:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:4-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:4–11:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a></p>\n<h3>To fulfil God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16-Matt8:17\">MAT 8:16–8:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:4\">ISA 53:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:15-Matt12:17\">MAT 12:15–12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:21\">LUK 4:21</a></p>\n<h3>To bring glory to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:4\">JHN 11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:31\">MAT 15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>To show Jesus to be the Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:22\">ACT 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:3-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:3–11:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:19-Luke7:22\">LUK 7:19–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:36\">JHN 5:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:25\">JHN 10:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:37-John10:38\">JHN 10:37–10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:42\">JHN 11:42</a></p>\n<h2>Varying responses to Jesus Christ's miracles</h2>\n<h3>Terror and fear</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:41\">MRK 4:41</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:25\">LUK 8:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:34\">MAT 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:15\">MRK 5:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a></p>\n<h3>Wonder and amazement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:36\">LUK 4:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:23\">MAT 12:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:43\">LUK 9:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Faith and gratitude</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:37\">LUK 19:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:18-Mark5:20\">MRK 5:18–5:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:38-Luke8:39\">LUK 8:38–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:15-Luke17:16\">LUK 17:15–17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:38\">JHN 9:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:11\">JHN 14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:30-John20:31\">JHN 20:30–20:31</a></p>\n<h3>Opposition and hatred</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:24\">JHN 15:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:20-Matt11:21\">MAT 11:20–11:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:13\">LUK 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24\">MAT 12:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:22\">MRK 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15\">LUK 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:10-John12:11\">JHN 12:10–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:37-John12:38\">JHN 12:37–12:38</a></p>\n<h2>Limitations on Jesus Christ's miracles</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ restricted his miracles because of superficial faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:23-John2:24\">JHN 2:23–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:38-Matt12:39\">MAT 12:38–12:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:29\">LUK 11:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:1-Matt16:4\">MAT 16:1–16:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:11-Mark8:12\">MRK 8:11–8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:18\">JHN 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:30\">JHN 6:30</a></p>\n<h3>Miracles require faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:58\">MAT 13:58</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:5\">MRK 6:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:28-Matt14:31\">MAT 14:28–14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:20\">MAT 17:14–17:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's miracles performed through others</h2>\n<h3>Through the disciples during Jesus Christ's lifetime</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:15\">MRK 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:2\">LUK 9:1–9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:38\">MRK 9:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:49\">LUK 9:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a></p>\n<h3>Through the apostles after Jesus Christ's ascension</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:6\">ACT 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:16\">ACT 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:10\">ACT 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:12\">ACT 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:8\">ACT 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:6-Acts8:7\">ACT 8:6–8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:11\">ACT 19:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:12\">2CO 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Through the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:10\">1CO 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28-1Cor12:29\">1CO 12:28–12:29</a></p>",
